               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                     <p>በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አሐዱ፡ አምላክ። ዳዊት። ዝውእቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ መዝሙራት፡ ዘዳዊት። ነቢይ፡ ወንጉሠ፡ እስራኤል።ወአኅተመ፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ኢዮብ፡ ሉዶልፍ፡</p>
                     <p>“In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit, one God. David. This is the Book of the Psalms of David. The Prophet and King of Israel. And Hiob Ludolf had it printed with God’s help”.</p>
                     <p>I) [መዝሙረ፡ዳዊት“Psalms of David”] (pp. ፫-፻፷፩ [<locus target="#3"/>-<locus target="#161"/>]) II) መኃልየ፡ነቢያት፡ ወጸሎቶሙ።“The Canticles of the Prophets and Their Prayers” (pp. ፻፷፪-፻፸፯ [<locus from="162" to="177"/>]) III) መኃልየ፡መኃልይ። “Song of Songs” (pp. ፻፸፰-፻፹፮ [<locus from="178" to="186"/>]) IV) ጸሎተ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ። “Prayer of Jesus Christ”,Mt <locus target="#18"/>:<locus from="25" to="30"/> (p. ፻፹፯ [<locus target="#187"/>])</p>
                     <p>V) ወከመዝኬ፡ ጸልዩ፡ አንትሙ።“And You Should Pray Like This”, Pater noster in Ethiopic (p. ፻፹፯ [<locus target="#187"/>])</p>
                     <p>VI) ጸሎተ፡ ነግህ።“Morning Prayer”(p. ፻፹፯ [<locus target="#187"/>]) </p>
                     
                     
                     
                  </summary>
                
               </msContents>
